# qactl repo rules

## The agent-shaped contract (don't break it)
- `--json` on every command emits the raw envelope; keep it lossless.
- Real exit codes: 0 only on `status` ok/warning, non-zero otherwise.
- stdin (`-`) / `--file` / inline accepted for any text payload arg.
- Every destructive/mutating subcommand is gated by `--yes` and refuses
  off a TTY without it. New destructive commands MUST add the gate.
- One envelope shape across `jira` / `confluence` / `jenkins`.

## Groups & layout
- Native (edit here): `jira` / `confluence` / `jenkins` under `qactl/`.
- Vendored, delegated by `qactl/__main__.py` (don't refactor their
  internals to "match" — keep them liftable): `cli`/`nc`/`gnmi`/`rc`/
  `setup` (the `dnctl/` package) and `ixia` (`ixiactl/` + `ixia*/`).
  Fixes to those belong upstream conceptually; keep changes minimal and
  isolated to the vendored tree.

## Secrets
- NEVER commit credentials. All tokens resolve at runtime from the
  environment (`ATLASSIAN_*`, `JENKINS_*`). No `.env`, no defaults that
  embed a token, none in code/docstrings/tests/issues.

## Issues (gh)
- Bugs/change requests arrive as `gh` issues. Triage on read: confirm
  the repro (command + exit code) before fixing.
- One issue → one branch → one PR. Label `bug` / `enhancement` /
  `needs-info`. Close via the merge (`Closes #N`), not manually.

## Concurrency (worktrees)
- Multiple agents may run against this repo at once. NEVER share one
  checkout — a `git checkout`/`switch` in one agent yanks the working
  tree out from under another mid-edit (lost/garbled work).
- Each agent/task gets its own `git worktree`. Create one off `main`
  before editing: `git worktree add ../qactl-<n> -b <branch> origin/main`
  (or `git worktree add ../qactl-<n> <existing-branch>`). Work, commit,
  push, and open the PR from there.
- `main` stays checked out in the primary clone; don't `checkout` other
  branches there. Rebase your worktree onto the latest `main`
  (`git fetch origin && git rebase origin/main`) before the PR so a
  parallel merge doesn't make your PR revert someone else's work.
- Clean up when merged: `git worktree remove ../qactl-<n>` +
  `git branch -D <branch>`. `gh pr merge --delete-branch`'s local step
  fails while the branch is in a worktree — remove the worktree first,
  or just delete the remote branch and prune.

## Branches / commits
- Direct commits to `main` are allowed; `main` stays releasable.
  Per-issue branches (`fix/<n>-slug` / `feat/<n>-slug`) are still fine
  when you want review or CI first, but are no longer required.
- Small, focused, imperative subjects ≤72 chars referencing the issue:
  `fix: gate jira comment delete on --yes (#4)`.

## Push / PR / releases
- Push directly to `main`, or open a PR when you want CI/review first.
  No force-push to `main`.
- Keep `main` linear (squash-merge PRs). Tag `vX.Y.Z` after notable
  changes and bump the version the CLI reports.

## Don't
- No edits outside this repo. No secrets anywhere. No `--no-verify`.
